<section id="fs-idm189717568">
<para id="fs-idm467594992">In this lesson, developed by and included with the permission of <link url="https://teachrock.org/about/">TeachRock</link>, students will examine 10 primary source documents to answer the essential question: In what ways and to what extent did the Vietnam War change American culture, society, and values?</para>
<para id="fs-idm196784144"><emphasis effect="bold">Suggested Sequencing:</emphasis></para>
<para id="fs-idm234320128">Use this Lesson with the <link class="target-chapter" document="m83582">Did U.S. Media Provide Fair and Accurate Coverage of the Tet Offensive?</link> Point-Counterpoint following the <link class="target-chapter" document="m83570">Kent State</link> Narrative to discuss the increase of anti–Vietnam War sentiments in the United States into the 1970s.</para>
<para id="fs-idm236974992"><emphasis effect="bold">Resources:</emphasis></para>
<para id="fs-idm179303792">Visit <link url="https://teachrock.org/lesson/americans-respond-vietnam-war-document-based-question-activity/?_sf_s=DBQ&amp;post_types=lesson,people,video,image,article">TeachRock’s website</link> to access this lesson and accompanying materials.</para>
</section>
